Modeling Details

Data Source: Central Valley Floodplain Evaluation and Delineation (CVFED) HEC-RAS hydraulic model refined for use in the NOAA-NMFS Winter Run Chinook Salmon life cycle model

High quality habitat defined by:

  • Channel depth > 0.2 m and < 1.5 m
  • Velocity <= 0.15 m/s

Sutter Bypass

The Sutter Bypass is divided into four sections:

  • Section 1 - To Moulton Weir
  • Section 2 - To Colusa Weir
  • Section 3 - To Tisdale Weir
  • Section 4 - Below Tisdale Weir

Area is in square meters.

Yolo Bypass

The Yolo Bypass is divided into two sections:

  • Section 1 - Fremont Weir to Sacramento Weir
  • Section 2 - Below Sacramento Weir
